counterharm_transformed:
Okukola ekitundu ky’ekika ekirala eky’okukwata ebikolwa eby’okukuba n’ebikolwa mu DataFrame, oyinza okukozesa enkola eno wano wansi:

```python
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.base import BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin

class ColumnSelectTransformer(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def __init__(self, columns):
        self.columns = columns

    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self

    def transform(self, X):
        if not isinstance(X, pd.DataFrame):
            X = pd.DataFrame(X)
        return X[self.columns]

def test():
    iris = datasets.load_iris(as_frame=True)
    simple_features = Pipeline([
        ('cst', ColumnSelectTransformer(['sepal length (cm)', 'sepal width (cm)'])),
    ])
    X = iris.data
    transformed_data = simple_features.fit_transform(X)
    print(transformed_data)
```

Eno enkola enkulu ey’okukola ekitundu ekikwata ku nkola ey’okukuba n’ebikolwa eby’okukozesa mu DataFrame. Oyinza okukozesa enkola eno mu pipeline y’omulimu ogw’obulungi mu machine learning. Kale, ensonga enkulu y’okukola enkola eno ye okukwata ku columns ez’oyagala okukozesa mu DataFrame nga tokubako drop rows ezine missing values, kubanga eno esobola okuleeterera obuzibu bw’okuba n’ebikolwa ebitali bituufu mu data y’oyinza okukozesa.

original_input:
To connect to a MySQL database using PHP, you can use the following code snippet:

```php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "username";
$password = "password";
$dbname = "database_name";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}
echo "Connected successfully";

// Close connection
$conn->close();
?>
```

